Yes, today I flew this plane.
First complaint: We need cute flight logs. Black is too boring, and what they call pink is actually salmon red.
I have always wanted to fly since I was little.
Today my dream came true... I flew a plane today. I still can't believe it.
FlightAware data.
I plan to give it another try on Saturday. The weather doesn't look good now, but it's only Monday today.
It seems that challenges in this area are already starting to show up. Due to the FAA's stance on certain drugs, I may find it difficult to obtain my medical certification.
This is not impossible, but it will require a lot of time and a significant amount of extra work.
While this is somewhat disappointing, it's just another problem to solve, and currently, it does seem solvable. It's just going to take a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges lie ahead for me:
FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
If I ever get the chance to customize the tail number of my airplane, it has to be some variant of N1337_, where _ represents any available letter character.
Of course, the sun will continue to rise without me, ha ha. That's just disappointing.
I have to fly again. But this weather is really not cooperating.
Welcome to the world of general aviation! 😜
Based on the ads on YouTube that they think I should see, the videos recommended to me, and the comments, I feel that airlines tend to be conservative in their tracking.
