#TeaganAir
The flight logbook has officially been started. I have 2.3 hours of flying time now ^_^
#TeaganAir
If I were to describe what it feels like to fly a small aircraft, I would say it's like riding a combination of a motorcycle/atv and a boat at 4000 feet in the air.
On the ground, conditions can change rapidly. There is a certain level of instability on the ground, which requires a motorcycle/atv.
Additionally, you might not know that when driving a plane on the ground, you use your feet to control direction, not the joystick. It's the rudder pedals and brakes you use. It's not like driving a car.
In the air, you will feel turbulence and shaking, much like sailing a boat on water. While you can control the plane, sometimes the air currents can make your head spin, so you need to adapt to flying in the air, just as sailors adapt to sailing.
There's also a random fun fact about this:
Flying is very tiring. Today my back and legs are sore, feeling as if I had gone to the gym.
This is far from just a Sunday drive. To me, a novice, it feels more like a sport than a cruise.
Dear friends, Happy Saturday. Welcome to 4,000 feet in the air.
Tomorrow I will fly again, and we will practice stall and slow flight.
The weather today was not very stable but super fun. We practiced slow flight and stalls. Our ground speed dropped to 16 mph while our airspeed was still at 65 mph.
Today the weather was clear, though a bit foggy at high altitude, the view was still fantastic.
